    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Boltzmann machines are very similar to HNs where some cells are marked as input and remain hidden. Input cells become output as soon as each hidden cell update their state (during training, BMs / HNs update cells one by one, and not in parallel).</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">This is the first network topology that was succesfully tained using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simulated_annealing" target="_self">Simulated annealing</a> approach.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Multiple stacked Boltzmann Machines can for a so-called <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep_belief_network" target="_self">Deep belief network</a> (see below), that is used for feature detection and extraction.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
