        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">DNs are DCNs reversed. DN takes cat image, and produces vector like { dog: 0, lizard: 0, horse: 0, cat: 1 }. DCN can take this vector and draw a cat image from that. I tried to find a solid demo, but the best demo is on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rAbhypxs1qQ" target="_self">youtube</a>.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
